   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Product Return Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes product returns by category, reason, customer type, and season. We focus on high-return items, financial impact, and likely root causes to help operations and product teams reduce return rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Analyze return patterns across products, categories, and time periods.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Quantify the financial impact of returns on revenue.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify root causes and recurring return reasons.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Segment return behaviour by customer type.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Generate actionable recommendations to reduce return rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Product returns erode margins, increase logistics costs, and signal product or experience issues. Understanding why returns happen enables targeted fixes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"In e-commerce, return rates can exceed 20-30%. Even small reductions save significant cost and improve customer satisfaction.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **6,000 orders** with return status, reason, and financial details.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 6000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CATEGORIES = [\\\"Electronics\\\", \\\"Clothing\\\", \\\"Home & Garden\\\", \\\"Sports\\\", \\\"Books\\\", \\\"Toys\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"RETURN_REASONS = [\\\"Defective\\\", \\\"Wrong Size\\\", \\\"Not as Described\\\", \\\"Changed Mind\\\", \\\"Damaged in Shipping\\\", \\\"Better Price Found\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CUSTOMER_TYPES = [\\\"New\\\", \\\"Returning\\\", \\\"VIP\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CAT_RETURN_RATES = {\\\"Electronics\\\": 0.12, \\\"Clothing\\\": 0.28, \\\"Home & Garden\\\": 0.08, \\\"Sports\\\": 0.10, \\\"Books\\\": 0.04, \\\"Toys\\\": 0.14}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cat = rng.choice(CATEGORIES, p=[0.25, 0.25, 0.15, 0.15, 0.10, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    price = max(5, round(rng.normal({\\\"Electronics\\\": 200, \\\"Clothing\\\": 55, \\\"Home & Garden\\\": 80, \\\"Sports\\\": 65, \\\"Books\\\": 18, \\\"Toys\\\": 30}[cat], 30), 2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    returned = int(rng.random() < CAT_RETURN_RATES[cat])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    reason = rng.choice(RETURN_REASONS) if returned else None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if cat == \\\"Clothing\\\" and returned:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        reason = rng.choice([\\\"Wrong Size\\\", \\\"Not as Described\\\", \\\"Changed Mind\\\"], p=[0.45, 0.25, 0.30])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cust_type = rng.choice(CUSTOMER_TYPES, p=[0.35, 0.45, 0.20])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"order_id\\\": f\\\"ORD{i+1:05d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"order_date\\\": rng.choice(dates),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"category\\\": cat,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"price\\\": price,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"customer_type\\\": cust_type,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"returned\\\": returned,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"return_reason\\\": reason,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"order_date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"order_date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"order_date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Return rate: {df['returned'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values:\\\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nReturned with no reason: {((df['returned']==1) & df['return_reason'].isnull()).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Not returned with reason: {((df['returned']==0) & df['return_reason'].notna()).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"returns = df[df[\\\"returned\\\"] == 1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total orders: {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total returns: {len(returns):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Return rate: {len(returns)/len(df):.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Revenue lost to returns: ${returns['price'].sum():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nReturn rate by category:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(df.groupby(\\\"category\\\")[\\\"returned\\\"].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).map(\\\"{:.1%}\\\".format))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Univariate Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"category\\\")[\\\"returned\\\"].mean().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Return Rate by Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Return Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"returns[\\\"return_reason\\\"].value_counts().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Return Reasons\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"customer_type\\\")[\\\"returned\\\"].mean().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[2], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Return Rate by Customer Type\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_ylabel(\\\"Return Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Bivariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Return reasons by category\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"reason_cat = pd.crosstab(returns[\\\"category\\\"], returns[\\\"return_reason\\\"], normalize=\\\"index\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"reason_cat.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", stacked=True, ax=ax, colormap=\\\"Set3\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Return Reason Distribution by Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Proportion\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=\\\"upper left\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Financial impact of returns\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"impact = df.groupby(\\\"category\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_revenue=(\\\"price\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    returned_revenue=(\\\"price\\\", lambda x: x[df.loc[x.index, \\\"returned\\\"] == 1].sum()),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return_rate=(\\\"returned\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").sort_values(\\\"returned_revenue\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"impact[\\\"loss_pct\\\"] = impact[\\\"returned_revenue\\\"] / impact[\\\"total_revenue\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Financial Impact by Category ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"impact\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Seasonal return patterns\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"monthly_returns = df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"returned\\\"].mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.plot(monthly_returns.index, monthly_returns.values, marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"coral\\\", linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Monthly Return Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Return Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xticks(range(1, 13))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"contingency = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"category\\\"], df[\\\"returned\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"chi2, p, dof, expected = stats.chi2_contingency(contingency)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Chi-square test (return rate vs category): χ²={chi2:.2f}, p={p:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Return rates differ significantly across categories: {p < 0.05}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Clothing has the highest return rate (~28%)**, driven primarily by \\\"Wrong Size\\\" — a classic fit problem.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Electronics returns are costly in absolute terms** due to higher unit prices.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **\\\"Wrong Size\\\" and \\\"Not as Described\\\" are the most actionable return reasons** — better product descriptions and size guides could reduce them.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Books have the lowest return rate** (<5%), making them low-risk products.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Customer type shows only minor return rate differences,** suggesting returns are product-driven, not customer-driven.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data with simplified patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No multi-item order structure (each row = one order).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No cost-of-return or restocking fee data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No product-level granularity within categories.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Invest in size guide improvement for Clothing** — virtual try-on or better measurement tools.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Improve product descriptions and photos** to reduce \\\"Not as Described\\\" returns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Implement quality checks for products with high defect return rates.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Track per-SKU return rates** to identify specific problem products.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Analyze return timing** — how many days after purchase do returns happen?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Looking at return rate alone without financial impact.** A high-return, low-price category may matter less than a moderate-return, high-price one.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Treating all return reasons the same.** \\\"Defective\\\" is a product quality issue; \\\"Changed Mind\\\" is a purchase behaviour issue.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Not distinguishing between controllable and uncontrollable returns.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Punishing customers for returns** instead of fixing root causes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Ignoring return fraud patterns** in high-return segments.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Calculate the \\\"net revenue\\\" per category** after removing returns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Identify the single most impactful fix:** which combination of category + reason would save the most money?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Build a simple logistic model** to predict whether an order will be returned.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Add a \\\"repeat returner\\\" flag** and study whether some customers are serial returners.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Estimate the cost of free return shipping** and compare it to the \\\"Changed Mind\\\" return volume.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m016\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Return rates vary dramatically by category,** with Clothing leading due to sizing issues.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **The most actionable return reasons are Wrong Size and Not as Described** — these are preventable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Financial impact analysis matters more than return rate alone** for prioritization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Reducing returns by even 2-3% can significantly improve margins.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
